DESCRIPTION
Extend the workflow schema and add the shared registry that live execution builds on. Per-stage `runner` (a name into the registry, or an inline command) + an optional run-level default runner. Per-stage `gate` block: `checks` (deterministic hard-veto runners), `seats` (model votes) or a `tier` ref, `pass_threshold`, `max_rounds`, `abstraction`. New shared seat/runner registry file (rename .etude/gates.yaml; it is a runner/seat registry, not gate bindings) with a Go parser: seat invocations, tier presets (L1-L4), quorum. No hardcoded phase names anywhere. Design: docs/plans/product/live-execution.md (Summary of decisions 2-4).

